<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A San Diego man who police suspect robbed an East San Diego apartment that was 
being fumigated died Wednesday at Villa View Hospital, a coroner's spokesman 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Willie Davis, 40, was taken to the hospital in critical condition early Tuesday 
when he was found collapsed in an alley connecting 43rd Street and Van Dyke 
Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
Authorities said Davis entered a two-story apartment building in the 3700 block 
