<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTH BAY DIGEST: TRASH-HAULING CONTRACT AWARDED; 
</P>
<P>
LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Rancho Palos Verdes City Council has awarded a five-year contract to Ivy 
Rubbish Disposal to collect trash in the Portuguese Bend neighborhood. The 
contract also calls for curb-side recycling. 
</P>
<P>
Ivy, which had been contracting individually with area homeowners to haul 
trash, will distribute bins for recyclable newspapers, bottles and aluminum 
cans. The firm will begin collecting these items April 1. 
</P>
<P>
Waste Management of North America Inc. serves other areas of the city. 
</P>
</TEXT>
