<HEADLINE>
<P>
TOROS CAGERS BATTLE FOR HOST HONORS IN CCAA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PAUL McLEOD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Cal State Dominguez Hills men's basketball team can secure its playoff 
future with a pair of victories this week. 
</P>
<P>
Wins over visiting Cal State Bakersfield tonight at 7:30 and Cal Poly San Luis 
Obispo on Saturday night at 8:05 will assure that the Toros will play host to 
the California Collegiate Athletic Assn. postseason tournament March 4-5 
</P>
<P>
Dominguez Hills (18-7) is tied with UC Riverside (21-4) for the CCAA lead at 
10-2. If the conference race finishes in a tie, the tiebreaker would come down 
to each team's record against Bakersfield, which is in third place. Riverside 
lost at Bakersfield last week, so a pair of Toro wins over Bakersfield would 
put the tournament in Carson. PAUL McLEOD 
</P>
</TEXT>
