<HEADLINE>
<P>
TOROS GET 1 HIT, SCORE 7 RUNS, TOP RIVERSIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cal State Dominguez Hills needed only one hit to score seven runs in the 
seventh inning in a 7-1 victory Wednesday over UC Riverside at Toro Field. The 
victory improved the Toros' record to 2-0 in the California Collegiate Athletic 
Assn. and 4-4-1 overall. 
</P>
<P>
Rick Davis pitched a three-hitter and struck out 13 to improve to 3-0. The 
senior right-hander has struck out 53 batters in 38 innings. Davis took a 
no-hitter into the sixth inning. The only run he gave up was a leadoff homer in 
the seventh. 
</P>
<P>
The Toros, who had only four hits, struck back in the bottom of the seventh 
with help from the Highlanders. Riverside's Doug Pierce, working on the 
shutout, walked the first two batters, then loaded the bases with an 
intentional walk following a sacrifice. A squeeze brought home the tying run, 
and catcher Mike McCarthy followed with a two-run single. An error, another 
squeeze and a wild pitch brought in the final runs. 
</P>
<P>
The Toros will play their annual alumni game Saturday at 1 p.m., then resume 
CCAA play Monday at home against Cal Poly San Luis Obispo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
