<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL SOCCER ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
SERRA GIRLS BEAT GRANITE HILLS ON PENALTY KICK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In a sudden-death round of tie-breaking penalty kicks, forward Andrea Gormican 
scored the winning goal as Serra defeated Granite Hills, 1-0, in the first 
round of the San Diego Section 3-A girls' soccer playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
"I hate to see a game won like that," Serra Coach Laurie Berger said. "I'd 
rather have a goal." 
</P>
<P>
Berger said the game was scoreless in regulation because of missed 
opportunities. 
</P>
<P>
"Granite Hills played a good tough game but couldn't score," Berger said. "They 
were very aggressive." 
</P>
<P>
Serra (9-8-4), which will meet San Dieguito Saturday, went undefeated in the 
Eastern League (7-0-3). 
</P>
<P>
Granite Hills finished 10-6-6. 
</P>
<P>
On other Class 3-A girls' games: 
</P>
<P>
Torrey Pines 6, Castle Park 0 -- Center forward Danielle Napoli scored two 
goals for Torrey Pines (14-4-2), which took advantage of a defensive mistake to 
take a 2-0 halftime lead. Castle Park finished 10-7-4. 
</P>
<P>
Mt. Carmel 1, Helix 0 -- Junior forward Nicole Hall scored 8 minutes into the 
game to give Mt. Carmel (11-7-6) the victory over Helix (7-9-3). Goalkeeper 
Heather Petterson had her 14th shutout. 
</P>
<P>
Poway 1, Hilltop 0 -- Poway's Kyle Clark scored with 15 minutes left off an 
assist by Alison Gibson. Goalkeeper Wendy Kevan had a save for Poway (14-4-5). 
Hilltop is 12-5-2. 
</P>
<P>
Boys 
</P>
<P>
Division 3-A first round 
</P>
<P>
Poway 3, Castle Park 1 -- Eric Hill scored one goal and had two assists to lead 
Poway (15-4-3) over Castle Park (16-7-0). Hill's goal was assisted by Kevin 
Legg. Poway's other two goals were by Kevin Arthur and Ryan Nutting. Poway led, 
1-0, at halftime. 
</P>
<P>
Mt. Carmel 2, Madison 0 -- Fullback Travis Cottle scored midway through the 
first half, and forward Joey Plewak scored with 15 minutes left for Mt. Carmel 
(15-3-3). Madison is 9-6-3. 
</P>
<P>
Sweetwater 1, Serra 0 -- Julio Roman scored off a corner kick from Gabriel 
Pulido with 10 minutes left. Daniel Topete recorded his 12th shutout for 
Sweetwater (17-3-2). Serra is 11-6-4. 
</P>
<P>
Bonita Vista 2, El Capitan 1 -- Bonita Vista advanced with a 18-3-1 record. Tim 
Von Feldt scored on a penalty kick in last 5 minutes for El Capitan (10-9-4). 
</P>
</TEXT>
