<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOUSING TOO EXPENSIVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Denise Hamilton's Feb. 9 article, "Easing the Squeeze," really hit home. 
</P>
<P>
Our family moved to California from Albuquerque, N.M., 10 years ago. Like the 
others in your article, my father received a job offer he couldn't refuse. 
</P>
<P>
My parents sold their home, which was middle-of-the-road but comfortable, to 
move to California -- and not be able to afford a shack. My sister followed. 
Now our neighbors and friends are selling and moving to Oregon. 
</P>
<P>
My sister can't raise a family of five in her three-bedroom home and can't 
afford to move up. So she's moving away. I don't have two incomes to support a 
house, so I'm renting mine out and moving away also. 
</P>
<P>
My parents are retiring here by themselves, with the family and neighborhood 
moving away. Is Ventura doomed to become a retirement community? 
</P>
<P>
RICK HOWIE 
</P>
<P>
Ventura 
</P>
</TEXT>
