<P>
UC IRVINE PLAYS HOST TO CS LONG BEACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN WEYLER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UC Irvine has won five of its last six basketball games and will finish the 
regular season with a four-game home stand that begins tonight at 7:30 when the 
Anteaters play host to Cal State Long Beach. 
</P>
<P>
A sweep would guarantee Irvine at least a tie for second in the Big West 
Conference, which would be a remarkable feat considering Irvine's 3-5 start in 
conference play. The Anteaters are 11-12 overall and 8-6 in the Big West. 
</P>
<P>
Long Beach (12-12, 9-6) had won four in a row before getting routed at Las 
Vegas Monday night by 18th-ranked UNLV, 104-74. In the first meeting this 
season, Long Beach won, 75-70. JOHN WEYLER 
</P>
