</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
All 10 players were injured when the bus carrying the Augusta (Ga.) College 
women's basketball team to the Big South Conference tournament at Radford, Va., 
collided with a flatbed truck just inside the South Carolina line. 
</P>
<P>
Also hurt were the student manager, the coach and an assistant coach. 
</P>
<P>
Coach Lowell Barnhart, 56, who was driving the bus, was taken to the Medical 
College of Georgia, along with players Krysti Boeck, 19; Debbie Grist, 20, and 
Mary Chavous, 22, a college spokesman said. All four were in fair condition. 
</P>
<P>
