<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTSIDE DIGEST: VENICE; 
</P>
<P>
RENT CAMPAIGN PLANNED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Venice Renter's Canvass, a tenants organization, is launching a campaign 
from Saturday to March 25 to keep Venice affordable. The group will canvass 
door-to-door to gain support for rent control in Los Angeles, for federally 
subsidized housing and to fight gentrification. 
</P>
<P>
Canvassers will meet for a brief orientation and distribution of materials at 
9:30 a.m. on Saturdays at 609 California Ave. For more information, call (213) 
392-2128. 
</P>
</TEXT>
