<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: MONTEREY PARK; 
</P>
<P>
A COURT, NOT A JAIL PLANNED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Board of Supervisors formally reassured Monterey Park on Tuesday that the 
county plans to build a $45-million Children's Court in that city, not a new 
jail. 
</P>
<P>
The city's redevelopment agency tentatively agreed Feb. 10 to sell four acres 
to the county for $3.5 million for construction of the court. But some 
officials expressed concern that the site might be used for a jail because it 
is next to the county's women's jail, the Sybil Brand Institute, supervisors 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The supervisors directed that a letter be written to Monterey Park, affirming 
the county's intentions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
