<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: AZUSA; 
</P>
<P>
PACT WITH IRWINDALE OKD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council has unanimously approved an agreement with Irwindale to help 
the city defray any costs for law enforcement or street repairs that might be 
necessary if the Los Angeles Raiders move to Irwindale. 
</P>
<P>
Under the pact, Azusa would be reimbursed for all police costs for traffic and 
crowd control on game days or for other stadium activities. 
</P>
<P>
The agreement will also provide for a three-year monitoring period for traffic 
impacts in Azusa, after which the cost of any needed street improvements would 
be split between the cities, with Irwindale paying for 90%. 
</P>
</TEXT>
