<HEADLINE>
<P>
FISHING: IT WAS NO HOLIDAY FOR FISH: ANGLERS MADE HEAVY CATCHES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Dan Stanton 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Presidents Day was no holiday for the fish. 
</P>
<P>
Anglers who took advantage of the long holiday weekend caught a variety of fish 
that put lumps into the sacks. 
</P>
<P>
Halibut and sculpin made up most of the catches, with the deep-water rock cod 
boats scoring limits on two-day trips. 
</P>
<P>
Redondo Sportfishing's Sea Spray was drifting at Twin Roads and 18 anglers 
reeled in halibut from 10 to 25 pounds. 
</P>
<P>
Long Beach Sportfishing's Southern Cal fished Catalina Island for rock cod in 
an area not fished for a month and within two hours anglers decked a limit of 
cows and lings. 
</P>
<P>
Fishing aboard the Annie B barge, Otto Koval of Long Beach was using a two-hook 
leader with cut squid and reeled in two halibut. Knowing they were hooked well, 
he bounced them to the deck instead of waiting for the net. 
</P>
<P>
The Cabrillo Marine Museum will have an open house Saturday from 10 a.m. to 5 
p.m. in honor of the L.A. Parks and Recreation Centennial Celebration. 
</P>
<P>
A guided tour will give a view of the marine lab's support systems. 
</P>
<P>
Also for viewing will be some of the exotic fish caught in local waters this 
winter. 
</P>
<P>
South Bay Catches: 
</P>
<P>
Arnold Fofa of Santa Monica caught the whopper of the week aboard the Spitfire 
off Sunset Beach, a 31-pound halibut. 
</P>
<P>
Bob Tyler of West Los Angeles, fishing at Catalina Island aboard the Southern 
Cal, won the jackpot with a 28 1/2-pound cow cod. 
</P>
<P>
Dee Clay of Redondo Beach, fishing at Hidden Reef on the Blackjack, won the 
jackpot with a 25-pound cow cod. 
</P>
<P>
Bob Sullivan of Santa Monica, on the Redondo Special, caught a 16 1/2-pound 
halibut. 
</P>
<P>
Myron Ackerman of Long Beach, at Catalina aboard the Southern Cal, landed a 
16-pound cow cod. 
</P>
<P>
Dave Parke of Torrance, aboard the Sea Spray, won the jackpot with a 15 
1/2-pound halibut. 
</P>
<P>
Fish Reports: 
</P>
<P>
At Marina del Rey Sportfishing: The Spitfire, fishing the bay for halibut, 
returned with 14, plus 300 sculpin and 12 sand bass. 
</P>
<P>
The Betty O deep-water rock cod trip produced 195 groupers. 
</P>
<P>
At Redondo Sportfishing: The Blackjack fished Hidden Reef and garnered 200 
reds, 1 lingcod and 1 cow cod. 
</P>
<P>
The Sea Spray worked Twin Roads and sacked 600 sculpin, 28 halibut and 21 sand 
bass. 
</P>
<P>
The Redondo Special fished the Flats and chalked up 185 sculpin and 17 halibut 
on a half-day trip. 
</P>
<P>
At 22nd Street Landing: The Monte Carlo worked White's Point and sacked 139 
sculpin, 28 sand bass, 2 calico bass and 1 sheepshead. 
</P>
<P>
The Freedom tried San Nicholas Island and returned with a limit of 330 rock cod 
and 4 cow cod. 
</P>
<P>
At L.A. Harbor Sportfishing: The Matt Walsh half-day trip to Horseshoe Kelp and 
Shallow Rocks chalked up 27 sculpin, 15 sheepshead, 10 half moon and 2 
rockfish. 
</P>
<P>
The Grande 85 on a two-day trip to Cherry Bank had limits of 500 rock cod, 10 
cows and 1 ling cod. 
</P>
<P>
The Annie B barge had a weekend count of 976 queenfish, 450 mackerel, 220 
jacksmelt and 2 halibut. 
</P>
<P>
At Long Beach Sportfishing: The Southern Cal fished outside the east end of 
Catalina and returned with a limit of rock cod, 285, plus 4 cows. 
</P>
</TEXT>
