<TEXT>
<P>
Viacom Inc: The New York-based communications and entertainment company posted 
a loss of $123 million for 1988, compared to a $161-million loss in 1987. 
Revenue for the year increased 25% to $1.26 billion. For the fourth quarter, 
the firm reported a loss of $26 million, versus a loss of $49 million a year 
earlier. Revenue in the quarter rose 34% to $355 million, boosted by domestic 
syndication of "The Cosby Show." 
</P>
