<TEXT>
<P>
In other 2-A matches: 
</P>
<P>
Woodbridge 4, Garey 0 -- The Warriors scored three second-half goals, two by 
John Szczuka, at home. Bruno Matturrano scored from 30 yards out 15 minutes 
into the second half to give the Warriors (11-4-5) a 2-0 lead. Szczuka scored 
his first goal on a header 20 minutes into the second half. He scored from 10 
yards out to give Woodbridge a 4-0 lead. Scott Schmidler scored 15 minutes into 
the match as the Warriors (11-4-5) led, 1-0, at halftime. Goalie Eric Mooberry 
made eight saves for the Warriors. Woodbridge will play Ridgecrest Burroughs 
Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Kennedy 4, Arroyo Grande 3 (penalty kicks) -- Fighting Irish goalie Jerry 
Vargas made a diving save on a penalty kick by Jose Quintana to preserve the 
victory at Kennedy. The two teams were scoreless through regulation, two 
overtime periods and sudden death. Vargas made 15 saves, including two penalty 
kicks, for Kennedy (16-4-3). 
</P>
<P>
Esperanza 5, Paraclete 0 -- Daran Martinez scored two goals and Horcio Villa, 
Mike Marageti and Troy Duncan one for visiting Esperanza (15-3-2), which plays 
Kennedy Friday in the quarterfinals. 
</P>
