<P>
CABLE FIRM REVEALS PLANNED RATE INCREASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dimension Cable Services, which serves about 100,000 customers in south Orange 
County, has announced that its monthly basic rate will be going up $2 effective 
April 4. 
</P>
<P>
In conjunction with the rate hike, Dimension Cable will be expanding the number 
of basic service channels. The rate increase will help offset the cost of the 
increased programming and other operating expenses, according to General 
Manager Richard Anderson. The current basic rate is $16.95 per month. 
</P>
<P>
Dimension Cable Services, headquartered in San Juan Capistrano, is a division 
of Times Mirror Cable Television. 
</P>
