</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Police are investigating the death of a young Anaheim man whose body was found 
in a city street, the victim of either a homicide or a hit-run incident, they 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The body of Marco Antonio Murrieta, 18, of Anaheim was found Tuesday night 
about 10:35 in the 1000 block of East Balsam Avenue. Police said he apparently 
died of severe head injuries. 
</P>
<P>
"The exact cause of death has yet to be determined," Police Sgt. James George 
said. 
</P>
<P>
George said Murrieta was pronounced dead on the scene, but he declined to give 
further details. 
</P>
<P>
Anyone who saw the incident or who may have information about the case is asked 
to call Anaheim police at (714) 999-1900. 
