<P>
MAN DIES IN SIMI FREEWAY LEAP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Traffic on the Simi Valley Freeway was snarled today during the morning commute 
when a man jumped off a pedestrian bridge into an eastbound traffic lane and 
was killed, Los Angeles police said. 
</P>
<P>
Police said the death was being investigated as a suicide. The man, whose 
identity was not released, climbed over a safety fence on the pedestrian bridge 
that crosses the freeway east of Reseda Boulevard in Northridge and jumped 
about 9 a.m., police said. 
</P>
<P>
The man hit the cab of a tractor-trailer rig and was killed instantly, police 
said. The death caused traffic in the eastbound lanes to slow and back up about 
a half mile while the investigation took place. 
</P>
</TEXT>
