<HEADLINE>
<P>
SARHOOB, FORLITANO LEAD ARCADIA FIELD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A field of nine headed by Sarhoob and Forlitano was entered today to run in 
Saturday's $100,000-added Arcadia Handicap at Santa Anita. 
</P>
<P>
Sarhoob will be ridden by Chris McCarron and was assigned high weight of 120 
pounds for the 30th running of the one-mile race for 4-year-olds and up. 
Forlitano will be ridden by Patrick Valenzuela and was assigned 118 pounds. 
</P>
<P>
If all nine entries go to the post, the total purse will be $111,700 and the 
winner will earn $66,700. 
</P>
